playerinfo.electriceyrie.Birdsong=<b>1st:</b> Reveal an order card.<br><b>2nd:</b> Craft the order card for <style="vpone">1</style> if it has an available item.<br><b>3rd:</b> Add the order card to the matching Decree column.
playerinfo.electriceyrie.daylight=<b>1st:</b>  Resolve the Decree—recruit for each column with at least one card from left to right, then move in that way, then battle in that way.<br><br>    <b>-Recruit -</b> Recruit warriors, equal to cards in this column, in a matching clearing with a roost.<br><br>        -Clearing Ties - Recruit in such a clearing with the most enemy pieces, then fewest Eyrie warriors, then lowest priority.<br><br>    <b>-Move</b> - Move from the matching clearing you rule with the most Eyrie warriors. Move to an adjacent clearing with no roost—if all of them have a roost, move to the one with the fewest enemy pieces. Leave warriors to exactly rule the origin clearing or equal to cards in this column, whichever is higher.<br><br>        -Destination Ties - Move to such a clearing with the fewest enemy pieces, then lowest priority.<br><br>    <b>-Battle</b> - Battle in a matching clearing. The defender is the player with the most buildings. If this column has the most cards, deal one extra hit. <br><br>        -Clearing Ties - Battle in such a clearing with no roost, then most defenseless buildings, then lowest priority.<br><br>        -Defender Ties - Battle such a player with the most pieces there, then most victory points.<br><br><b>2nd:</b> Build Place a roost in the clearing you rule of highest priority with no roost. If you cannot place a roost, you fall into turmoil.
playerinfo.electriceyrie.evening=Score the <style="vptext">VP</style> listed on the rightmost empty space on the Roosts track.
